¦IN LOVING MEMORY OF
MUM, LILLIAN GRACE PINFOLD (NEE BOREHAM)
BORN INWORTH STREET, BATTERSEA ON JUNE 4TH 1914
PASSED AWAY OCTOBER 7TH 2008
AND GREATLY MISSED BY ALL"¬
¦In fond memory of
Our Founder Mrs June Mackay
Our Chairman John Perry
and Secretary Mrs Louise Perry (nee Conner)
from the members of the Brixton Dog Training Club"¼
®The FerrymanŌĆÖs Seat

The FerrymanŌĆÖs seat, located on the previous building at this site, was constructed for the convenience of Bankside
watermen, who operated ferrying services across the river.
The seatŌĆÖs age is unknown, but it is thought to have ancient origins.

Historic Southwark"«
